Chance the Rapper has disclosed that Jeremih will soon be discharged from the hospital. Jeremih was admitted in the Intensive Care Unit, ICU due to complications from COVID-19. Chance giving update on his Twitter page on Thursday said he spoke with Jeremih and he is doing well. His tweet read: “ I am filled with praise right now I just heard Jeremih’s voice on the phone for the first time in almost a month.” The rapper thanked everyone who prayed for Jeremih’s recovery and the medical staff, adding that, “he would be out of the hospital tomorrow.” “Thank you to the medical staff at northwestern and thank you to everyone who held him up in prayer even when it seemed so grim. We are a testimony,” Chance added.